An Act relative to notices by insurance companies.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 175 of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding after section
2 187H the following new section: -
3 Section 187I. Notwithstanding any other provision of law relative to the cancellation,
4 renewal or nonrenewal of an insurance policy, any insurance company may, with the agreement
5 of the named insured, provide such notice by electronic means.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect on passage.
